n inches per day et is calculated based on temperature solar radiation rainfall humidity and wind measurements reported from the weather station the daily reports from the weather station enable daily adjustment of schedules in all the system controllers something that would not be possible manually this can result in significant water savings for example a 1996 study of the oval lawn indicated that use of maxicom with et based scheduling resulted in a 27 water savings in addition to irrigation scheduling we use weather station data for other applications we calculate degree days for use in our integrated pest management ipm programs and we compute chill hours each year for use in plant selection weather station archive 2001 weather station archive 2002 weather station archive 2003 weather station archive 2004 weather station archive 2005 weather station archives 2006 weather station archive 2007 weather station archive 2001 stanford university all rights reserved stanford ca 94305 drupal site designed and developed by wired moon in partnership with lbre
